directory: crates/ctx-summarize
domain: Binary+library crate implementing the `ctx-summarize` runner: turns leaf source files into `.ctx` summaries and rolls them up bottom-up into `rollup.ctx`, via a pluggable Agent (LLM completion, subprocess-based) and Fs (filesystem) seam. Consumed as a CLI that resolves targets from either a ctx-access task cache or an explicit path list.
edit_notes:
  - Layering is fixed: cli (argv/io) -> runner (pure orchestration) -> fs/agent (seams); runner must never depend on cli.
  - cpath.rs's `.context/<src>.ctx` / `.context/<dir>/rollup.ctx` layout is duplicated in ctx-access pending a planned ctx-core unification — changes there must be mirrored.
  - fs.rs's scope_matcher (`.ctxignore` + `target/`) must stay in sync with ctx-scan's walker; it defines what runner/cli treat as in-scope.
  - agent.rs's SubprocessAgent stdin/stdout JSON contract is the model-agnostic boundary any CTX_AGENT_CMD script must implement.
  - Depends on ctx-core via relative path "../ctx-core"; must stay in the same workspace layout.
children:
  - src/: Crate implementation — CLI, runner orchestration, Fs/Agent seams, path/cache utilities, error types.
  - tests/: Integration suite exercising runner ordering, gating, and Fs/Agent contracts via fakes and a real subprocess.
invariants:
  - intent.md is read-only everywhere in this crate — read as rollup input, never written.
  - All fallible operations return SummError variants; no panics on malformed input, missing files, or bad task ids.
  - runner writes leaves before rollups in strict leaf-to-root order; runs over 50 targets are blocked unless explicitly approved via `--approve`.
  - Path validation rejects absolute/empty/`.`/`..`/null-byte paths before any file is touched.